cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the analysis of data from a crowdfunding platform, specifically Kickstarter, to predict whether a creator will deliver all rewards in a project on time or not, and to estimate accurate reward delivery duration. This involves the use of machine learning techniques and the extraction of novel features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the analysis of social networks and online communities. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deal with topics related to online communities, user behavior, and data analysis.
